<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,969,1322]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1049,1075]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
Three ocelli present, lateral ocelli separated by about their diameter from eye margin. Eyes at most slightly emarginate, eye bridge absent, eyes practically bare. Laterotergite setouse, other pleura bare, except for prothoracic sclerites. Midpleural pit present. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[845,853,1146,1160]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">5</subScript>
running very close to C, first sector of Rs tiny, transverse, r-m scarcely visible; medial fork long, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[779,787,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[873,881,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">2</subScript>
diverging before middle of wing. Wing membrane largely covered with macrotrichia. Male tergite 9 devoid of distal projections bearing strong spines found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[259,429,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chiletrichinae">Chiletrichinae</taxonomicName>
. Gonostylus simple. Female cerci 2 segmented, first segment shorter than second; no sclerotized spermathececae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
